was AMAZING. I lovelovelovelovelovelove my boyfriend.&nbsp;

Very sleepy now.&nbsp;

and happy.

I figured out my taxes.&nbsp;

I owe the government $128.&nbsp;

What a bunch of crap.&nbsp;

Fuck the goddamned government.

Proud of my boys.&nbsp;

Birthday on Thursday.&nbsp;

Surgery on Monday.&nbsp;

Emotional.&nbsp;

Gotta go.

"ER docs don't know their ass from their esophagus."

You're goddamned right.&nbsp;

Of course, nobody seems to really know what's wrong with me.&nbsp;

Meanwhile, I keep undergoing horrible, invasive, humiliating, and painful tests so every doctor I see can keep saying "Well, the tests are all clear. Gee, I guess we really don't know what's wrong with you."

No shit.&nbsp;

Here's something cool I just realized :&nbsp; 

Brooke Smith played Catherine Martin (the girl in the pit) on The Silence of the Lambs.&nbsp; 
Brooke Smith also plays Dr. Ericka Hann on Grey's Anatomy.&nbsp; 
So someone from my favorite movie also plays someone on my favorite show.&nbsp; 
Cool, huh? 





Yup. I thought so.

Kayla's first day of school was on Wednesday. We went in early so she could get familiar with her classroom before the other kids got there. Once the other kids arrived and class started I tried to get her involved, but she was hesitant. She had a couple minor freakouts during circle time, where she would run back and hide in the corner. I hugged her and talked to her and got her calmed down. Then we went back to the circle, but we didn't sit in the cirlce. We just sat back and watched what the rest of the class was doing. We watched them take roll, and we watched show-and-tell. After show-and-tell was over it was lunch time. The TA helped Kayla and shoewd her the lunch routine. Wash your hands, take your tray, take a napkin, and your silverware, and find a seat. I sat with Kayla through lunch and ate together. We sat at a table with Miss Heather, her teacher, and she explained the classroom rules and routine to us. After lunch I decided that Kayla should get used being in class without me being there, so I got ready to leave. When she realized that I was really leaving she had a major freak out./ She was screaming and crying "Mommy! Mommy! Mommy!" and was&nbsp; clinging tight to me. She wouldn't let me go. The teacher actually had to pull her off from me. It broke my heart, but she had to learn. So I left. I called the school a little bit later to check on her and the TA told me that she was doing great. She calmed right down shortly after I left. So Day One went ok. Yesterday she was really excited to go to school. She picked out her show-and-tell, and packed her backpack by herself. We went to school, and I helped her find her locker and put her stuff in it. She took her show-and-tell to the circle. She sat in the circle with her class, and did her show-and-tell when it was her turn (she brought her purple purse with her big Charlie Brown and her little Charlie Brown inside). Then she showed me what she needs to do to get ready for lunch. I got her settled in at a table with Miss Lacey, the TA, and then I left. She didn't cry at all that time, and when I went back to pick her up at three her teacher told me she had a wonderful day, and that she was making lots of friends at school. She was my big brave girl, and didn't cry at all yesterday. I am so proud of my big girl, going to school. She doesn't have school on Fridays. Next week she'll only go on Monday, because she's goingon vacation with my mom, which I am extremely happy about because it gives me and David five solid dys together. I just hope that we don't have to go through all the crying and adjusting again at school once she comes back from Missouri.&nbsp;


Yesterday I hung up Kayla's school lunch calander on the fridge with magnets, and I got all teary eyed with happiness and pride. I'm so proud of her.&nbsp;

My baby's going to school.&nbsp;

She's really growing up now.

We were watching Bobby's World on the tv today. Cute little Bobby, and his mom, with her gee-darn Midwestern accent there, donchya know.&nbsp;

Man, I used to watch that when I was little tiny. It's so wierd that Kayla is watching it too. It's so wierd to even think that that show is like twenty some years old. Really dates my childhood. Makes me feel older.&nbsp;

I have an infected cuticle on my index finger on my right hand. It's swollen up huge and hurts really bad, and has a big bandaid on it, and it 's really hard to type.&nbsp;





Terrrrrrrible cutting and burning tomorrow.&nbsp;

I am so glad David is going to be with me.&nbsp;

He is my rock.&nbsp;

I really couldn't live without him.&nbsp;

I love him.&nbsp;

We're getting married someday, donchya know.&nbsp;

Renee Danielle Bolema. Whaddya think of that?

Renee Danielle Chartrand-Bolema.&nbsp;
Renee Bolema.&nbsp;
Renee Chartrand-Bolema.&nbsp;



Which sounds better?

I'm leaning towards just Bolema, but Kayla's last name is Chartrand, and I wanted to kind of tie things together. You know, Kayla Chartrand, David Bolema, Renee Chartrand-Bolema. I'd have the connecting name and tie everybody together.&nbsp;

Whatever. I've got some more time to think about it. Maybe she'll be like seventeen when we get married like I was when my mom remarried and she'll understand us having different last names.&nbsp;

But I really don't want to have to wait fourteen years to get married.

So, I've been feeling really down lately. I just lay in bed all day, don't get dressed or brush my hair. It's a pretty&nbsp;grizzly sight. .&nbsp; 

Anyway, I finally decided to leave the house to get candy so I could go home and lay in bed all day eating candy. I went to Walgreens and ran into Mike Valley. I looked completely like shit, no makeup, wearing glasses, bushy brows because I haven't plucked them in weeks, and ran into super-hot-used-to-be-a-really-good-friend-former-junior-year-of-highschool-crush Mike Valley.&nbsp; 

We used to hand out during science class all&nbsp;the time. We'd sit in the lab and hang out and I'd try to be all super cool, and I used to try really hard to look really hot, and I thought maybe I had a chance with him. He was so cute, really skinny and pale, always dressed really nice and had his hair styled nice, had really good taste in clothes and music, and he was really incredibly smart, and funny. He was great.&nbsp; 

I got up the guts to ask him out one day, and he turned me down flat. He was really nice about it. He told me that I was a really sweet girl, and that any guy would be lucky to have me, but I'm just not his type. Well, I thought, whatever. I tried.&nbsp; 

That was kind of the end of our friendship. Everything became very awkward after that.&nbsp; 



Turns out he was gay. I thought he was just a little effeminate, but nope. Gay.&nbsp; 

I guess I was just oblivious.&nbsp; 

And I know it doesn't really matter if I looked good or bad when I ran into him today, because it's not like he would think "Oh man, she's gorgeous! Why didn't I go out with her in highschool? I was such an idiot!" Because he's gay. But I at least wanted him to have a good impression of me if we were ever to meet again. Now he thinks I'm just one of these horrible looking Holton trash whores. A nobody, going nowhere, stuck. And fucking ugly to boot.&nbsp; 

Goddamnit.&nbsp; 

Now I'm going to have to get all glammed up and go to Walgreens and get some film developed or something. And chat with him for a minute and tell him all these lies about what I'm doing with my life, so he won't think I'm just a trashy Holton piece of shit.

And to all a good night . . .&nbsp;


Off to St. Louis in the morn.&nbsp;

Much to do.&nbsp;


Adios.
